   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>TRUTH LESSONS LEVEL ONE LESSON SEVEN A KEY VIEW OF THE OLD TESTAMENT 1 FROM ADAM TO NOAH OUTLINE In Adam is seen God s redemption: Receiving the promise of God s redemption.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Experiencing the anticipated redemption of God: Through the substitution of the bleeding sacrifice.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Through the union of the covering skins.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>In Abel is seen God s way of redemption acceptance by God through the sacrifice: Abel working and living for God a feeder of sheep.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Abel worshipping God according to God s revelation.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>In Enosh is seen man s need for God and man s calling upon Him to enjoy God s riches.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>In Enoch is seen one who was redeemed and who walked with God on the pathway of redemption.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>In Noah is seen one who walked with God and worked with God to meet the need of that generation: Walking with God.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Building the ark.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Changing the age through his life and work.</S>
   </TEXT>
